    caption: [Biosynthesis of phosphatidic acid. A fatty acyl group is activated by formation of the fatty acyl–CoA, then transferred to ester linkage with L-glycerol 3-phosphate, formed in either of the two ways shown. Phosphatidic acid is shown here with the correct stereochemis- try at C-2 of the glycerol molecule. (The intermediate product with only one esterified fatty acyl group is lysophosphatidic acid.) To conserve space in subsequent figures (and in Fig. 21–14), both fatty acyl groups of glycerophospholipids, and all three acyl groups of triacylglycerols, are shown projecting to the right. c21LipidBiosynthesis.indd Page 849 03/10/12 11:29 AM user-F408 c21LipidBiosynthesis.indd Page 849 03/10/12 11:29 AM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop],
