  "21-19": (
    caption: [Regulation of triacylglycerol synthesis by insulin. Insulin stimulates conversion of dietary carbohydrates and proteins to fat. Indi- viduals with diabetes mellitus either lack insulin or are insensitive to it. This results in diminished fatty acid synthesis, and the acetyl-CoA aris- ing from catabolism of carbohydrates and proteins is shunted instead to ketone body production. People in severe ketosis smell of acetone, so the condition is sometimes mistaken for drunkenness (p. 959). c21LipidBiosynthesis.indd Page 850 03/10/12 11:29 AM user-F408 c21LipidBiosynthesis.indd Page 850 03/10/12 11:29 AM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 850],
