    caption: [Biosynthesis of sphingolipids. Condensation of palmitoyl- CoA and serine (forming (cid:3)-ketosphinganine) followed by reduction with NADPH yields sphinganine, which is then acylated to N-acylsphin- ganine (a ceramide). In animals, a double bond (shaded light red) is cre- ated by a mixed-function oxidase before the final addition of a head group: phosphatidylcholine, to form sphingomyelin, or glucose, to form a cerebroside. We begin with an account of the main steps in the biosynthesis of cholesterol from acetate, and then discuss the transport of cholesterol in the blood, its uptake by cells, the normal regulation of cholesterol synthesis, and its regulation in those with defects in cholesterol uptake or transport. We next consider other cellular components c21LipidBiosynthesis.indd Page 860 03/10/12 11:29 AM user-F408 c21LipidBiosynthesis.indd Page 860 03/10/12 11:29 AM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 860],
